# DEPLOY — {{project_name}}

This guide takes you from "empty server" to a running {{project_name}} on your own hardware.

> Prerequisites assume Linux (Ubuntu / Debian / Fedora) but anything that runs Docker will do. Adjust paths and package names accordingly.

## Is it alive? (60-second check)

Once deployed, {{project_name}} is healthy when:

```bash
curl -sf http://localhost:${HTTP_PORT:-8080}/healthz
```

returns 200. The full deploy walkthrough is below.

